@Comment: MOT decides that Chi will write to his dad. Chi is a competent writer and could probably compose his own letter , but Mot directs him from beginning to end. Mot digresses for long periods about Chi's poor penmanship and spelling and about a friend. She comes across as unnecessarily critical of Chi who does a great job. Nevertheless it seems clear that Mot is concerned about Chi's performance and success.
